    Direct Known Subclasses:

    Enclosing class:
    SetterInjection

    public static class SetterInjection.SetterInjector<T>
extends IterativeInjector<T>
    Instantiates components using empty constructors and Setter Injection. For easy setting of primitive properties, also see PropertyApplying.PropertyApplicator.

    Note that this class doesn't cache instances. If you want caching, use a Caching.Cached around this one.

    Author:
    Aslak Hellesøy, Jörg Schaible, Mauro Talevi, Paul Hammant

                              String notThisOneThough,
                              boolean optional,
                              MethodParameters... parameters)
                               throws AbstractInjector.NotConcreteRegistrationException
        Constructs a SetterInjector
        Parameters:
        key - the search key for this implementation
        impl - the concrete implementation
        monitor - the component monitor used by this addAdapter
        prefix - the prefix to use (e.g. 'set')
        useNames - use parameter names
        notThisOneThough -
        optional - not all setters need to be injected
        parameters - the parameters to use for the initialization
        Throws:
        AbstractInjector.NotConcreteRegistrationException - if the implementation is not a concrete class.
        NullPointerException - if one of the parameters is null
